<module status="bronze">
  <h>ergonyms</h>
  <p>Ergonyms are <a href="?xx=nouns/names">names</a> identifying groups of people – teams,
    organisations, institutions, companies, clans, etc.</p>
  <p>Like other kinds of name, ergonyms can be classified into two grammatical types – <ul>
      <li>ergonymic <a href="?xx=nouns/proper_nouns">proper nouns</a> – <g>Misneachd</g>
        <en>[name of pressure group]</en>, <g>CNAG</g>
        <en>[name of government agency]</en></li>
      <li>ergonymic <a href="?xx=nouns/name_descriptions">name-descriptions</a> – <g>An Comunn
          Gàidhealach</g>
        <en>The Highland Association</en>, <g>Comhairle nan Leabhraichean</g>
        <en>The Gaelic Books Council</en></li>
    </ul>
  </p>

